Issue: Email sent multiple times. Action Taken: As per Microsoft Advise, following steps were done to resolve the issue: 1. Please check for the latest occurrence of the issue so the latest duplicate emails; 2. Archive them and attach them to the reply; 3. Take the header of both duplicate emails and paste them one by one to https://testconnectivity.microsoft.com/ at the Message Analyzer section. Click on analyze header and copy the message ID from both of them separately; 4. Check if the message IDs are identical or different; 5. In case of being identical run an extended message trace after the message trace. Once again you will select the date to be bigger than 7 days or even more than that if the messages are older so that will be included in the result. And once again, do not forget to check the box saying 'Include routing details’; 6. In case the message IDs are not identical you will perform the steps from the previous point after both message IDs; 7. Please access and run the Microsoft Office Configuration Analyzer Tool for several of the affected users: https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=36852; 8. After successfully installing OffCAT, please start your Outlook client, and then run the OffCAT application, selecting Outlook as program to scan (Outlook will need to be open and stay open when running the scan); 9. When the scan is complete, there will be a menu/option to Export the results of the test in a OFFX file; 10. Please save the results in the that format, then archive it in a .ZIP file and forward the archive, so we can analyze the results; 11. Take a print screen on the Inbox where the 2 duplicate emails are visible together and send it to us as well Resolution: User now confirmed that emails are not duplicated. Hence proceeding with the closure of the ticket.

column6: Fallo Software: MENSAJE ERROR INICIO OUTLOOK
column11: SITA resolution:- Please note on first visit FE got to the site to check set as the user reported when open the outlook it shows an error message FE found there was a problem with the executable archive .exe seems to have a problem due virus on system FE tried to recover the software on site but had not success, as the FTP from ESP need s to be the specific one downloadable for (IBERIA), as per user confirmation a new visit to the site is required so FE can download and install the FTP, today the Fe was not able to download the FTP due problem on the local Network as it presented a lot of limitations Please note on second visit FE got to the site to try to install FTP ESP Iberia "Office2013STDSP1"- FE contacted Iberia Service Desk, spoke with Samuel. FE tried to install the new office version downloaded from the ESP FTP Iberia "Office2013STDSP1", it is not compatible with Windows XP, the new office version required another OS most recent, this was informed to ESP Angello (Security Update for Microsoft Outlook 2010 (KB4011273)). Could not be installed. IF new office is required must be compatible with the WIN XP 32B OS or replace the whole unit as there is no more support for Win XP Please note on third visit FE got to the site to do the uninstallation from old damaged device and install the new device Dell 780 purchase locally as requested, FE started to work on the back up from device once he got to the site once the FE received the new device he tried to install the IB image but the user informed they do not have the image locally and FOS techs do not carry the image it must be provided on site by IB office FE spoke with Angello Otarolla and confirmed this, and informed about the situation local user confirmed they will try to get the image and will confirm once he got it to go back to the site to be able to install the new CPU case needs to remain open Please note on fourth visit FE got to the site to complete the installation from New Device Dell 780 S/N: 9XCYPM1 with the image provided for download FE could complete the image as requested, FE called IBM Row spoke with Martin Air Canada FE could configured user profile Outlook, IBTERM, configured Office and Windows and completed the back up on new device after FE completed the new PC installation user Carlos Frisone did all tests on device confirmed it is fully operational working correctly and this case can be close.
Se prueban diferentes configuraciones y no nos fucnciona desde ningún equipo, el usuario que crea las macros debe hacerse cargo de su funcionamiento.

column6: User not able to view IATAs on Iberia Agencies admin tool
column11: Issue: User was not able to view IATA 7820760 & 7821342 on Iberia Agencies Admin portal Analysis: We identified that the CIF and group details for these IATA are not present in our database which is why he was not able to view them Impact: With no access to the IATAs, user was not able to manage their access and hence these agencies would not be able to access the application. This could impact revenue for Iberia Steps Taken to Resolve: We followed up with Salesforce team to add the relevant details to their system after which the user was able to access the IATAs Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No): No. This issue was not with our application, but with Salesforce team Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No. Agencies need to make sure that they are getting correct data updated in Salesforce system ---------------------------------------------------- Did not receive update from Angeles, but from Damian where he has mentioned that he is following up with Salesforce responsible person and will update us when he gets any response. -------------------------------------------------- We have asked Angeles to tell us who can update this data in Salesforce and she is talking with the account manager. ---------------------------------------------------- We have sent an email to Paz Velasco to check in Salesforce system, the groups for these IATAs. ----------------------------------------------------- We verified and informed the user that the IATAs are not associated with any group which is why they are not able to view them on screen. They need to check with Salesforce to see if correct information is updated in the system.

column11: Issue: Email sent multiple times. Action Taken: As per Microsoft Advise, following steps were done to resolve the issue: 1. Please check for the latest occurrence of the issue so the latest duplicate emails; 2. Archive them and attach them to the reply; 3. Take the header of both duplicate emails and paste them one by one to https://testconnectivity.microsoft.com/ at the Message Analyzer section. Click on analyze header and copy the message ID from both of them separately; 4. Check if the message IDs are identical or different; 5. In case of being identical run an extended message trace after the message trace. Once again you will select the date to be bigger than 7 days or even more than that if the messages are older so that will be included in the result. And once again, do not forget to check the box saying 'Include routing details’; 6. In case the message IDs are not identical you will perform the steps from the previous point after both message IDs; 7. Please access and run the Microsoft Office Configuration Analyzer Tool for several of the affected users: https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=36852; 8. After successfully installing OffCAT, please start your Outlook client, and then run the OffCAT application, selecting Outlook as program to scan (Outlook will need to be open and stay open when running the scan); 9. When the scan is complete, there will be a menu/option to Export the results of the test in a OFFX file; 10. Please save the results in the that format, then archive it in a .ZIP file and forward the archive, so we can analyze the results; 11. Take a print screen on the Inbox where the 2 duplicate emails are visible together and send it to us as well Resolution: User now confirmed that emails are not duplicated. Hence proceeding with the closure of the ticket.

column11: Issue: Falla el proceso porque un fichero que nos envian de fuera ha llegado sin registro de pie. Impact: Se retrasa la carga de la información que contiene el fichero. Root Cause: El sistema de recepción de ficheros, cuando el fichero es muy grande, cataloga el fichero antes de que esté completamente transmitido y lanza el proceso finalizando con error al faltar parte del fichero. Steps Taken: Se revisa que el fichero ya lo tenemos completo, y se ha ejecutado otro proceso posterior correctamente, por lo que se borra el proceso fallado.

Root Cause: The F49 process has been modified to invoice through a new company (Universal Pay) and there is a problem in canceling the retention after the definitive charge with the cards of the La Caixa-Debit type. Steps Taken: After limiting the problem, it is agreed with the Business group involved to close the incident as they will deal directly with the external Universal Pay provider. Issue: Se produce un cargo y una retención al cliente por el mismo importe. Impact: Reclamaciones e impacto en la imagen de la compañía. Root Cause: Se ha modificado el proceso F49 para facturar a traves de una nueva compañia (Universal Pay) y hay un problema al cancelar la retención tras el cargo definitivo con las tarjetas del tipo La Caixa-Debito. Steps Taken: Tras acotar el problema, se acuerda con el grupo de Negocio implicado cerrar la incidencia ya que lo van a tratar directamente con el proveedor externo Universal Pay.

That is the reason why you don’t receive an ACK response message with Resiber PNR. When the message is treated the flight sell is rejected with NO action code. I copy you the sequence that happened to a test PNR that you created: The message from the 22nd of January is rejected to a queue: ILLEGAL ACTION LINE 6 <QP: QK MADRMIB .HDQRMAA 222030 RQR HDQAA DQEFES/BB7B/99999999/DFW/1S/T/US 1SINGH/BUTCH TEST IB6166Q/AA8640Q18APR BOSMAD CS1/1725 0620/1 IB3876Q/AA8727Q19APR MADSCQ CS1/0725 0840 Is reprocessed manually: HDQRMAA .MADRIIB 241444 HDQAA DQEFES/BB7B/99999999/DFW/1S/T/US MADIB P6PPE 1SINGH/BUTCH TEST IB6166Q/AA8640Q18APR BOSMAD CH1 IB3876Q/AA8727Q19APR MADSCQ NO1 SSR OTHS IB KK/ CODESHARE FLIGHT OR CLASS INVALID Now, the flight is properly loaded on the system. Please, try to do a new reservation on that flight to see if everything is working properly. Thanks&Regards.

ISSUE: Daily Web Reports load failed. IMPACT: The Application performs the necessary calculation processes for the Reports that are presented in the Web Portal www.iberiacorporate.es and allow a Sales tool and follow-up to the managers and managers of the Business Unit. ANALYSIS: The process was failing because of the condition in the shell script which monitored the running session, according to the condition, there should not be 4 or more than 4 process running at the same time. RESOLUTION: The process was ran and successfully got completed. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: Yes, need to check if the number of parallel sessions can be increased. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: Yes, if the number of the session can be increased in the script.

Issue: [PAE] PNR’s no pasan por Cybersource Impact: PNR issue without CYBERSOURCE verification. Resolution: We reviewed the PNR’s mentioned in the excel attached in the mail chain below. We found there is an error “[77002] Undefined error->Error Cybersource ID: 77002, Message: Undefined error” traced in the logs cyersource.out. This is the reason the PNR doesn’t get accepted in the cyber source. Following is the error: PNR JQMLYK 21 Feb 2018 22:53:33,233 INFO - [ ParametersCandidateBOImpl::doPccLogic ] >> Scoring done: true, FraudMessages null: false 21 Feb 2018 22:53:47,480 INFO - [ CyberSourceBOImpl::getItems ] >> 0 : MIAIB08AA : MAD-RAK:RAK-MAD : Kara : Mcpherson 21 Feb 2018 22:53:47,497 INFO - [ CyberSourceBOImpl::isButtonEnabled ] >> Is isButtonPayment enabled: true 21 Feb 2018 22:53:48,055 ERROR - [ CyberSourceBOImpl::checkFraud ] >> 77002: Undefined error 21 Feb 2018 22:53:48,057 ERROR - [ CyberSourceException::trace ] >> afsService- JQMLYK-[77002] Undefined error->Error Cybersource ID: 77002, Message: Undefined error at es.indra.iberia.simpl.bo.CyberSourceBOImpl.checkFraud(CyberSourceBOImpl.java:211) at es.indra.iberia.simpl.bo.PaymentButtonFraudBOImpl.doFraudLogic(PaymentButtonFraudBOImpl.java:211) at es.indra.iberia.action.ajax.KeepPurchaseDataSecurePaymentAction.executeOk(KeepPurchaseDataSecurePaymentAction.java:313) at es.indra.iberia.action.ajax.GenericAjaxAction.execute(GenericAjaxAction.java:67) at org.springframework.web.struts.DelegatingActionProxy.execute(DelegatingActionProxy.java:113) at org.apache.struts.action.RequestProcessor.processActionPerform(RequestProcessor.java:484) Since there is a problem ticket raised to counter this error with reference id: PBI000000049154, we proceed to close this incident as it is already being investigated in the problem ticket mentioned. Can this incident be prevented: No

Issue: Automation "IB_Carga_Bajas_Email" failed on January 31 Impact: if this automation will not run then the unsubscriber email Id's will not ingest into the data extension and the unsubscriber will receive the unwanted communication from IBERIA, thus they can escalate the same, hence it can be an impact on IBERIA brand. Analysis: The automation failed due to file ageing Steps Taken to Resolve: Opened an incident with Salesforce help to know why automation failed and re-run the automation manually by setting file age limit from 12 to 24 hours so that there is no failure for next run. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No): No, because this failed due to file age (configuration) Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): Yes, this could have be prevented by setting file age limit to 24 hours instead of 12.

column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec2.ib : Swap area occupied 97.18%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column11: Issue: ELK - client node ibclogec2.ib was having high swap memory occupied. Analysis: After running for sometime elasticsearch client nodes have light memory leak thus they start consuming swap space quickly. Business Impact: If client node continue to occupy swap memory, it may leave elk cluster which might effect request and responses from kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec2.ib and client nodes shows up in the ELK cluster. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No). No, as client nodes have light memory leak thus after running for some time, they start occupying swap memory. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) : No, in elastic search client nodes have light memory leak as the background is build in Java, we can not prevent client nodes from consuming large swap memory after running for long time.

Issue: Error in execution of CLM_EXPORT file as file for 31st Jan 18 is not received from ICW Business Impact: Delay in file execution is critical to Iberia cards since it holds data of the active customers in Spain based on which business rules are created to calculate the accrued points, programs etc. Analysis: File arrived late due to which the sequence of the files have changed due to which IBCARDS was not able to identify the files with respect to the date and sequence number generated..Therefore manually re ran the member files. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Member's file to successfully process the file. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

column6: Revisar si las pasarelas de los mercados de Brasil y Reino Unido no presentan ningún problema
column11: 2/8/2018 9:19:11 PM, NIIT.prani, Issue Description : Check if the gateways of the markets of Brazil and the United Kingdom do not present any problem Business impact : No impact as all the ERRORS occurred are the genuine ones. Action taken: We have seen the trend for all the listed markets and found a slight increment in KO transactions for FR, IT and GB markets on 31st in comparison of 30th Jan’18 and reason could be the slight hike in total bookings. Also we have observed that all the ERRORS occurred are the genuine ones. No abnormality seen during this period. As we do not see any issues with these markets, we are closing this incident. There was communication going on with the user. Please find the attached mail for all the relevant information. 2/2/2018 6:34:25 PM, NIIT.prani, We have sent the below update to contact user. For more info, Please see the attached mail. "We have seen the trend for all the listed markets and found a slight increment in KO transactions for FR, IT and GB markets on 31st in comparison of 30th Jan’18 and reason could be the slight hike in total bookings. Also we have observed that all the ERRORS occurred are the genuine ones. No abnormality seen during this period. As we do not see any issues with these markets, Please confirm if we are good to close this incident. Below are few genuine ERRORS: Error_al_comprobar_el_resultado_de_autenticación_de_la_operación_en_curso Fondos Insuficientes CC_DENIED Respuesta_rechazado_de_CyberSource" 2/1/2018 11:48:39 PM, NIIT.rjha, We have been investigating the KO transactions for few markets from the below list and found that all the ERRORS occurred at different time-stamps caused by several reasons in which most of the reasons are genuine ones. We are investigating it further and also checking the trend for all the mentioned markets. We sent mail to Raul requesting downgrading the priority. Downgrading priority to medium after getting confirmation. We are further investigating. Mail attached. 2/1/2018 11:48:23 PM, NIIT.abansal, relevant stakeholders have been advised this is not issue anymore reducing priority as per attached email 2/1/2018 7:42:37 PM, NIIT.rjha, We checked current trend and it seems payment is working fine for given markets. We don't see any major problem. We are further investigating the root cause for this.

column6: Abrir incidencia por reparto erróneo de importe de Ancillaries de I2
column11: Issue: Consulta sobre importes de ficheros ancilleries de I2 Impact: Bajo Root Causes: Si analizamos por ejemplo al billete 4010731076 que se envió ayer: 060;01;4010731076; ; ;M9LPCC1A ;31/01/2018;7849447; ; ;00000003000;EUR2;00000003000;CCCA1000 ;00000003000 060;02;4010731076; ; ;M9LPCC1A ;31/01/2018;7849447; ; ;00000000000;EUR2;00000000000;CCCA1000 ;00000003000 Estos importes que marcamos en color se corresponden con el importe de la forma de pago a nivel contrato, en el cupón 1 viene la primera forma de pago, en el 2 viene la 2ª... así es cómo está diseñado este proceso, por eso veis que al final todo el importe lo tiene el cupón 1. Este proceso parte directamente de los ficheros en formato BSP, es antes del prorrateo a nivel cupón, no se dispone de ese valor para enviar. En la parte de IB el funcionamiento que está implementado tira directamente de Base de datos, dónde ya se tiene el prorrateo a nivel cupón, y por ello la información que se obtiene es distinta y si va el dato prorrateado. Steps taken: Se informa al cliente.

column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 92.01%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column11: Issue: ELK ibclogec1.ib client node was having high swap area occupied Business Impact: Kibana search can get impacted as the client nodes handle request and response from kibana. Analysis: Elasticsearch services were down on client node as a result of high swap memory area occupied. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node and it joined the cluster back. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No). No, as client nodes have light memory leak thus after running for some time, they start occupying swap memory. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) : No, in elastic search client nodes have light memory leak as the background is build in Java, we can not prevent client nodes from consuming large swap memory after running for long time.

El proceso falla porque no existe el factor millas clase. Steps Taken: Solicitud para modificar la fecha FMIFINI para la cia y la clase agrupada de la tabla BEACU.TACUFMI. Recibido el aviso que se modifico la fecha FMIFINI, relanzar el proceso desde el paso fallado. Termina OK.

column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 94.32%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column11: Issue: ELK - high swap area was occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib. Analysis: After running for some time client nodes consume swap memory. Thus it is required to restart the elasticsearch services. Business Impact: Users will not be able to make request and response from Kibana if client node leaves the cluster. Hence it is important that both the client nodes in cluster are up and running. Resolution: we restarted the elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib and it is up and running now. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to start services on client nodes. Can this incident be prevented: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to restart elasticservices on client nodes

Thus it is required to restart the elasticsearch services. Business Impact: Users will not be able to make request and response from Kibana if client node leaves the cluster. Hence it is important that both the client nodes in cluster are up and running. Resolution: we restarted the elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib and it is up and running now. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to start services on client nodes. Can this incident be prevented: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to restart elasticservices on client nodes

column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 92.33%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column11: Issue: ELK - high swap area was occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib. Analysis: After running for some time client nodes consume swap memory. Thus it is required to restart the elasticsearch services. Business Impact: Users will not be able to make request and response from Kibana if client node leaves the cluster. Hence it is important that both the client nodes in cluster are up and running. Resolution: we restarted the elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib and it is up and running now. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to start services on client nodes. Can this incident be prevented: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to restart elasticservices on client nodes

column6: Restart the virtual machine for GAUDIPR4
column11: Issue: Unable to login to the Hyperion GaudiPR4 platform. Impact The server was down because of which users were not able to login to the platform Later the scheduled reports also did failed to execute. Analysis: The virtual machine for GaudiPR4 was down,was not able to login to the RDC.when multiple reports were executing or multiple user logged in at the same time and the CPU performance reached 98-100% the services went down. Actions Taken: Opened a incident to Windows ES for Restarting the virtual machine for GAUDIPR4. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The services were restarted and therefore , no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The services were restarted and therefore , no issue with the application.

column6: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column11: Issue: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors. Impact: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis: As per the process we checked the database for errors/blocking session, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned dao logs for the specified errors. Resolution: Since the errors stopped appearing in the log and there were no blocking session in DB, so we are closing this INC. Problem Ticket Required: No, This is a alarm Incident which arrives when the system starts facing issues(it requires manual check), but the code handles the connections after some time duration.We need to check the health of the system through designated logs. Can this incident be prevented: No

LINUX_sun - ibclogec2.ib : Swap area occupied 91.51%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column11: Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec2.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec2.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.

Issue: In Semi-automatic notifications" that are dated Feb 5th , although user have "Rejected" them every day, they go out again. Impact: User was getting email alerts again and again for semi-automatic notification for same rejected flight. Analysis: As per analysis in lower environment there are many tables are impacted (dependant) by rejecting flight list. As per business logic user has to choose the reject cause option from the menu(Avisado Manualmente). After that related data will be update and delete from the tables e.g. ibc_notifications,ibc_semiaut_notif_pending,IBC_GROUPS_TAB,ibc_failed_notifications. Resolution: Found that the status in ibc_semiaut_notif_pending not been updated. We have updated the states than the flight stops reappearing. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED:NO: We will wait for this issue to replicate again in production, if this happens again then we will raise a problem ticket. CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED:NO:Its an intermittent issue. When user has rejected the flight thtough the portal may be few tables not get updated in db.

column6: AMO001 - FALLO AL GENERAR PDF EN AMOS APN1
column11: Análisis de impacto: No aplica Acciones realizadas: Simulamos la generación del informe con los filtros expuestos por la usuaria y generamos el infomre correctamente.Llamamos a la usuaria y no está. Hablamos con una compañera (APMIB.Méndez Alonso, Cecilia Patricia <APMIB.cpmendez@iberia.es>) y concluimos que el problema es de la configuración de memoria del pc del usuario que no soporta la generación del inofmre. Nos indica la usuaria que podemos cerrar la incidencia ya que comprobamos con ella que su pc es de 32 bits y no admite más de 1GB de memoria para AMOS. Nos indica que ya se encarga ella de hablar con su compalera y que la opción que le aconsejo de actualizar a 64 bits no lo ve claro ya que son de empresa externa a iberia, que mejor partirán los datos filtrando para que el volumen de memoria consumida sea menor Pruebas realizadas: No aplica

column11: 2.13 - We are checking with the PROS team on this. They advised to send them the weekly trend of memory usage of batch server. So we have already raised a ticket for Linux team to provide the necessary details. 2.9-Weblogic team explained that this needs to be checked with the LINUX team. 02.07 - As per the AFLS they suspect that the restart attempt made while the server was running already could have caused the high memory consumption. Since we could see stuck threads and exceptions post the server restart. Passing this issue to weblogic team to check is there any auto script which attempt to restart the servers or someone manually attempt to restart the server when they are already running. Please investigate why this issue occurred. 2.6-AFLS updated that there was an issue with VPN but now it has been resolved. They have restarted the batch.

column6: **REOPENED**[CIP] OB20243932 T9 fare has accrued points
column11: Issue: OB20243932 T9 fare has accrued points Impact: Only account OB20243932 Analysis: It has come to our knowledge that this issue is part of a major pending farebasis development on IBERIA. In this case, farebasis arrived to Cobol systems as VDNNNB/T9. As you know, T9 is the farebasis for discounted ticket. However, this system is not prepared to receive the slash (/), hence it automatically considered only the first part of the farebasis (VDNNNB) and assigned the code ‘00’ (eligible to accrue). Therefore, the ticket passed on to Comarch like that, with 00 code, and hence it accrue points. Resolution: We have already discussed this with the Business team (Ana de la Llave) and she has confirmed that no action should be made on the ticket. That is, the points that were incorrectly posted, are not to be withdrawn.

column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 100.00%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGro
column11: Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.

FE Name: Zain Hussain Date of intervention: 07/02/2018 & 16/02/2018 On site hours: 03:00 07/02/2018 Off site hours: NA Work done: The engineer has been onsite 07/02/2018 from 1:00 p.m. to 3:00 p.m. with a travel time of 30 minutes. The engineer has reviewed the equipment and executed a diagnosis of RAM and hard disk. In the verification tests a hard disk failure is obtained and a replacement of the hard disk drive is requested. The user has said that they need that position to work for what a supervisor has authorized to move a team close to the position so that the user continues working. The CPU PMIKQ02 is replaced by the CPU PMIKQ08 so that the user can continue working. The spare PC sent by Mulesol has been delivered to the Engineer. Today 16/02/2018 the engineer has spoken with the user of this incident but this time he has spoken with the head of Iberia CUP, and has commented that having replaced the equipment damaged by a team that did not use the incidence is resolved for them. Therefore, it is not necessary to install another spare equipment and do not want it since it will not be useful. The head of Iberia CUP was not in the conversation the other day, so it could have hurt the decision and does not want the team. We will bring the Spare back to Mulesol Workshop MAD Iberia User: Mati, Iberia CUP. Release Name: Mati, Iberia CUP.

column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 92.55%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column11: Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.

column6: LHRSBC - HFM CARGO IB - unable to retrieve
column11: Hi Richard, Fortunately we have found the cause which not let you to retrieve the template values. In the template, the column B14 retrieve the smartview connection name (HFMPROD_IAGCHFM), in this case, the connection name of the user who create the template, and your connection name for HFM prod is “HFM” (see the private connections panel). To correct this, you need to change your connection name. Second click on your connection and select “change name” to change it from ‘HFM’ to ‘HFMPROD_IAGCHFM’. Then refresh the template and you should see the correct values. Thanks and regards HFM Support Alternative contact point for any escalations: cmaroto@iberia.es or mbaranda@everis.com

Issue: Failure in load processing of CLM_Export file for 11th Feb 2018. Analysis: We found that there was a delay from ICW in sending the daily CLM file on 12th Feb 2018. Business Impact: Delay in file execution is critical to Iberia cards since it holds data of the active customers in Spain based on which business rules are created to calculate the accrued points, programs etc. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for CLM_export file to successfully process the file. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No) No, as the file arrived late from the source team due to some technical errors at their end which caused the ODI plan to fail. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) Yes, source team should send the required files on time in order to prevent such incidents.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

column6: Fallo en proceso semanal de infare
column11: Issue: we got an Error in process of obtaining the weekly file of infare Impact:If This PROCESS fails, user will not receive file. analysis: The infare weekly process only executes on Monday and it depends on the daily infare file that we download from INFARE server. This process begins at 9:00 and we got the file at 9:06 so for that reason the process failed resolution: We have re run the the below process sh /IBairprice/INFARE/infare_W/bin/sh/carga_IW.sh & and and got the Ok Email indicating that daily file of infare has successfully ran. Problem ticket required: NO, this is due to late arrival of the file.. Can this issue be prevented: NO, this is due to late arrival of the file.

column6: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column11: <ISSUE>:: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors.The logs genarted by Ibconecta showed that there were connectivity errors. <IMPACT>:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database and hence no new notifications from IbConecta <ANALYSIS>:: As per the support document incident we request DBA team to check the errors, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors but more often than not the connectivity is restored itself. <STEPS TAKEN TO RESOLVE>:: As said, we moitored the database for a while and the connectivity was restored. We checked in the logs to verify the connection. <PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? (Yes, No).>:: NO, because its a pseudo Alarm and we have already worked with Database team to extend the pool size. <CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED? (Yes, No)> :: No, Its an intermittent issue, when the databse connectivity is lost and Ibconnecta keeps polling for the connection.We had already asked DBS to increase the Pool size.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

Analysis:we have checked with ATOS and and find Resolution: we have raised Issue with ATOS and find that that there are users who have open the application up to 3 times and this is not operational because each session automatically closes when they have been using it for 1 hour without giving that error, in addition to saturating the connections to BBDD. we have asked the users Please try not to open new connections of the application unless it is strictly necessary, or if you are not using it frequently, close it when you finish the steps that you are doing. Although, we have already got confirmation from users that now they able to access application. Problem Ticket: No, as these issue occurs when multiple users face issue accessing the application, which leads to saturation of Database Preventive measures: No, It is solely based on Agents how they use the application.

the planned order will be converted to purchase requisitons when the requirement date is reached. There is a difference in the way MD01(MRP job) and MD03 (Single material planning) is run. MD03 screen values (like Modo planificación, Crear lista MRP, Crear solicitud de pedido etc..) will have priority over other configuration and variables in the system while in MD01, screen values are only considered as default values (i.e other system wide settings will be considered which should be the case). Thats why when you are MD03 and selecting the option 1 for Crear solicitud de pedido, the system is creating purchase requisition for future forecasted requirements now itself. Hope it clarifies your doubt. Let us know if you need more help. Thank you.

column11: Se llama a la usuaria para confirmar si podemos cerrar la incidencia ya que el problema se debia a la caida de sistemas de ayer 13 de febrero.

dia 13, se analiza la ase de datos para detectar posibles bloqueos, no apaprece ninguan sesion bloqueada. Se analiza el entorno rvisando todas las maquinas por si hubiera algun proceso que realentice la aplicaion, pero no se encuentra nada. Se accede a la aplicacion y se navega por ella por distintas opciones utilizadas frecuentemente por los equipos de reclamaciones sion detectar ningun problema. Se solicta mas informacion al respecto para tratar de detectar el error. dia 14, se informa por parte de los agentes que la incidencia se estuvo produciendo el dia 13 durante unas dos horas y que en esos momentos la aplicacion funcionaba con normalidad. Se analiza la plataforma y no se detecta nada anomalo. Dia 15, se analiza la plataforma a la misma hora que se reporto la incidencia por parte de los usuarios y no se detecta nada. Todos los procesos de los que es propietario el usuario administrador de siebel estan controlados pero existen en la plataforma otros procesos no controlados por Mantenimiento CRM y que podrian ser los causantes de un problema puntual de rendimiento Cerramos la incidencia.
Se comprueba acceso tras desbloqueo.

Problem Ticket : Not required as it is a network issue, after some it alerts stop generating. Preventive Measures : As it is a network issue so there is no as such preventive measure.

column11: [2/20/2018], NIIT.SKULYANA, Sent the anlaysis to digital business and proceeding to close the issue as it is normal application behaviour. 2/15/18 4:27:30 PM, NIIT.APRUSTY, FYI we had a similar incident which was resolved by CKI team. INC no is INC000000980462 2/15/18 4:24:47 PM, NIIT.APRUSTY, Hi Team, We see in the logs that the PAX had uploaded all the required documents when got AQQ_SELECTEE error message. Later he was successfully able to get the BC. We know as per the procedure, if the AQQ or ESTA is not OK, the host must re-send the information to the American TSA to answer if it allows the passenger to be billed or not. Can you Please check if the mentioned request was made or something missing from your end- so that we can communicate further to business. If everything OK, can you please provide some instances on that. Attached Screen. ================================== Hola equipo, Vemos en los registros que el PAX había cargado todos los documentos requeridos cuando recibió el mensaje de error AQQ_SELECTEE . Más tarde logró con éxito el BC. Sabemos que según el procedimiento, si AQQ o ESTA no están OK, el host debe volver a enviar la información a la TSA estadounidense para que responda si permite facturar al pasajero o no. ¿Puede verificar si se realizó la solicitud mencionada o falta algo de su lado, para que podamos comunicarnos más con el negocio? Si todo está bien, ¿puede dar algunas instancias sobre eso? Pantalla adjunta.

column6: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column11: <ISSUE>:: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors.The logs genarted by Ibconecta showed that there were connectivity errors. <IMPACT>:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database and hence no new notifications from IbConecta <ANALYSIS>:: As per the support document incident we request DBA team to check the errors, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors but more often than not the connectivity is restored itself. <STEPS TAKEN TO RESOLVE>:: As said, we moitored the database for a while and the connectivity was restored. We checked in the logs to verify the connection. <PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? (Yes, No).>:: NO, because its a pseudo Alarm and we have already worked with Database team to extend the pool size. <CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED? (Yes, No)> :: No, Its an intermittent issue, when the database connectivity is lost and Ibconnecta keeps polling for the connection.We had already asked DBA to increase the Pool size.

column6: OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT
column11: Issue: Error encountered during execution of IB Card Assignment out File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds data of the Card Assignment points, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Avios points against their Iberia Cards. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully send the IB Card Assignment file to IB Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.
Se comprueba acceso tras desbloqueo.

Se entra como administrador y se actualiza la aplicación.

column6: LINUX_sun - apliwebl1.ib : Pool JDBC Aeropuertos1^Aeropuertos1^IBCONECTPRO+bdl+ibutf8 no Activo. Avi
column11: Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections as the pool would have depleted. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: "####<ene 30, 2018 3:51:21 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1517323881002> <BEA-310002> <46% of the total memory in the server is free>" Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

Issue: we got an Error in process of obtaining the daily file of infare Impact:If This PROCESS fails, user will not receive file. analysis: we have investigated and find that file for the date 8/2/2018 is not available on the below loaction /IBairprice/INFARE/Infare_Diario/datos/input resolution: we have investigated the issue and find that INFARE daily process has fail due to late arrival of the file. we have re-run the below process sh /IBairprice/INFARE/Infare_Diario/bin/sh/infare.sh & and and got the Ok Email indicating that daily file of infare has successfully ran. Problem ticket required: NO, this is due to file has not present on the required location. Can this issue be prevented: No, File was not present on source location. we have investigated the issue and find that INFARE daily process has fail due to late arrival of the file. we have re-run the below process sh /IBairprice/INFARE/Infare_Diario/bin/sh/infare.sh &

column6: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column11: <ISSUE>:: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors.The logs genarted by Ibconecta showed that there were connectivity errors. <IMPACT>:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database and hence no new notifications from IbConecta <ANALYSIS>:: As per the support document incident we request DBA team to check the errors, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors but more often than not the connectivity is restored itself. <STEPS TAKEN TO RESOLVE>:: As said, we moitored the database for a while and the connectivity was restored. We checked in the logs to verify the connection. <PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? (Yes, No).>:: NO, because its a pseudo Alarm and we have already worked with Database team to extend the pool size. <CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED? (Yes, No)> :: No, Its an intermittent issue, when the databse connectivity is lost and Ibconnecta keeps polling for the connection.We had already asked DBS to increase the Pool size.

column6: [COM037] Los clientes no pueden ingresar. Es el servicio de IBPLUS.
column11: Issue: Unable to log in in IBPLUS via IB.COM Impact: CRITICAL. Affects all IBPLUS customers. Analysis: After analysis on IB.COM side, COM037 team are sending the request to ATOS and ATOS is returning an ORA 114 error related to DataBase. The issue is reported to ATOS at high priority and confirm that after restarting the JBOSS the issue is resolved. Resolution: The issue is resolved after restarting IBPLUS Jboss in ATOS. To verify resolution, we check in Splunk and errors have stopped since the time ATOS have applied the fix. Tested the login in IB.COM and it's also working fine. Pending to receive P1 report from ATOS to include it in the Remedy ticket.

Issue : Points expired for an OB user : OB20383184 Impact : Incorrect expiry of points would lead to an unnecessary hassle for the OB user. Analysis : Since these issues are dealt by the CIP team, we have passed on the snapshots received from Business to the CIP team for further investigation. Steps Taken to Resolve : Since these issues are dealt by the CIP team, we have passed on the snapshots received from Business to the CIP team for further investigation. CIP team had checked at their end & found that the expiry of points was expected & provided justification for the same. This was then passed on to the Business & they confirmed that they were satisfied with the justification & hence this stands closed. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No) : No, this is one of an Instance & hence no problem ticket required. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)> : No, this is one of an instance and hence, measures cant be taken at our end to avoid this.

column11: [26/02/2018] NIIT.mpsingh [issue]: [TRYsTJj50] Gift card consumes the balance without being used [Impact] 1 User [resolution] This is a known issue and should be raised as an enhancement [23/02/2018] NIIT.mpsingh This is a known issue and manual intervention will be required in order to claim the bono if the service has suffered timeout during the consumption. This abnormal behavior of BONO service occurs due to way the application is designed and resolution to this known issue is to implement an enhancement in the application. The same concern has already been conveyed to the business in the past as well. [2018/02/23] LEDA.lnavio: nos infoma IT que en este caso hubo un Timeout del servicio, pero ¿no debería haberse devuelvo el uso al bono? Debido a este timeout, el cliente se quedó con su bono consumido y sin poder usarlo de nuevo. [22/02/2018] NIIT.mpsingh Provided analysis to business as the issue is not in application but seems to be in infrastructure.

Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: ####<feb 21, 2018 7:31:07 AM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519194667617> <BEA-310002> <49% of the total memory in the server is free> ####<feb 21, 2018 7:35:16 AM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl1.ib> <Aeropuertos1> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519194916455> <BEA-310002> <65% of the total memory in the server is free> Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

column6: Escalado Job: LINUX_ibm - El job: X25OBIM2 con OrderID: 30ih9 del DataCenter: CTM_SERVER en la maqu
column11: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso X25OBIM2 porque no ha ejecutado el proceso X25OLST del que controla la condición. Impact: Medio, al no ejecutarse el X25OLST se retrasa la entrega del fichero IB-MERGER-LOADSTATS al proceso que lo explota y por tanto el producto final. Root Cause: El X25OLST no se ejecuto porque el proceso X25OI21 no tenia activiada la condicion FICI281-OK 2002. Steps Taken: Añadir la condicion FICI281-OK 2002 para que se ejecute el proceso X25OI21 y se ejecute el proceso X25OLST. Una vez ejecutado el X25OLST se borra el X25OBIM2 fallado.

column11: Issue : Filthy information seen to be sent as Response emails to the IBPLUS members. Impact : Words used in the response emails portrays a bad image of Iberia & the company can even be sued for the language used by the IBPLUS members. Analysis : Since the emails were supposed to be checked at ATOS end, an email was sent to them to look into this & investigate. Steps Taken to Resolve : Since the emails were supposed to be checked at ATOS end, an email was sent to them to look into this & investigate. It seems that one of ATOS testers have used this while testing the email template & had forgotten to remove it. This was corrected at their end. But later on after this was resolved, it was reported that the Response emails to be sent to Silver card holders are using the Clasica template. This also was corrected at ATOS end. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No) : No, this is one of an Instance & handled by the 3rd party & hence no problem ticket required. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)> : No, this is one of an instance and hence, measures cant be taken at our end to avoid this.

column6: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column11: Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: ####<feb 22, 2018 3:40:11 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519310411525> <BEA-310002> <71% of the total memory in the server is free> Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

column6: Escalado Job: LINUX_ibm - El job: X25OBIM2 con OrderID: 30nic del DataCenter: CTM_SERVER en la maqu
column11: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso X25OBIM2 porque no ha ejecutado el proceso X25OLST del que controla la condición. Impact: Medio, al no ejecutarse el X25OLST se retrasa la entrega del fichero IB-MERGER-LOADSTATS al proceso que lo explota y por tanto el producto final. Root Cause: El X25OLST no se ejecuto porque no se recibio el fichero ED04.LRESER.A180221. Steps Taken: Una vez recibido el fichero ED04.LRESER.A180221 se ejecuta el proceso D04OCHR. Ejecutandose toda la cadena de procesos hasta la ejecución del proceso X25OLST. Se borra el proceso X25OBIM2 que se encuentra fallado.

ANALISIS DE IMPACTO: Bajo Fallo en la carga de smart ACCIONES REALIZADAS: Se comprueba que ocurre y nos falta el fichero de inventory que se reclama ya que va con bastante retraso, cuando llega se procede a cargarlo de manera manual PRUEBAS REALIZADAS: Se realiza comprobación de que el procesos van correctamente y que las cargas en BBDD han ido correctas

column11: Issue : User unable to receive calls from the switchboard. Impact : User would not be able to function as an Agent & thereby will not be able to work/ add value to the Callcenter's customers. Analysis : Since the support of such instances is provided by the BT team, we have asked them to open an Incident at their end. User's ID was created by the BT team initially but she was unable to receive calls. Hence, this issue was further checked by the BT team only. Steps Taken to Resolve : Since the support of such instances is provided by the BT team, we have asked them to open an Incident at their end. Site code was provided as S654422 from our end to get it assigned to the appropriate technical department at BT's side. We have provided the user's details as well, so that they can speak to the User, as the credentials were created & provided by them to the user. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No) : No, this is one of an Instance & handled by the 3rd party & hence no problem ticket required. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)> : No, this is one of an instance and hence, measures cant be taken at our end to avoid this.
The Issue has been fixed. We had suggested the solution to user. Hence closing the ticket.

Issue: Error encountered during execution of IB Card Assignment out File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds data of the Card Assignment points, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Avios points against their Iberia Cards. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully send the IB Card Assignment file to IB Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

column11: Issue: ELK - NFS backup drive was running on high disk usage Impact: This will impact the backup process of ELK and can result in high disk usage on Data nodes as old indices will not be deleted Analysis: We had a request to restore an old snapshot which lead to high disk usage on backup drive. Resolution: To manage the space in NFS_drive we deleted the snapshot for the current week as indices were still alive. Archived the old snapshot backup-2018.01.22. Also, space on the backup drive is increased from 1TB to 4TB. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, problem ticket is not required as due to a request to restore old snapshot the space on Backup drive was high. This incident can be avoided?: Yes, can be avoided. Now we have allocated more space on the backup drive to avoid such issues in future.

column6: LINUX_sun - nfsla.ib : Filesystem datapro-ib_nfs_backup is occupied 90.08%.
column11: Issue: ELK - High NFS disk space. Analysis: we analyses that on the disk there were more number of snapshots that should not be there. Business impact: If there would be less space in the NFS drive then backup tool will not perform it's activities, thus there would be no snapshot creation, index deletion and archival. there could a huge impact of data mismanagement. Resolution: we removed the latest snapshot and archived the oldest snapshot so that we can have more space on NFS Disk. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as the disk space issue is not raised frequently. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as the NFS backup is includes snapshot and we don't have a fixed size of the snapshots.

Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. column11: Issue: Falla el proceso porque un fichero que nos envían de fuera ha llegado sin registro de pie. Impact: Se retrasa la carga de la información que contiene el fichero. Root Cause: El sistema de recepción de ficheros, cuando el fichero es muy grande, cataloga el fichero antes de que esté completamente transmitido y lanza el proceso finalizando con error al faltar parte del fichero. Steps Taken: Se localiza el fichero completo entre los recibidos en cmem y se fuerza su paso a las carpetas de /datos para que así se cargue y ejecute así el proceso de nuevo.

LINUX_sun - ibcloged1.ib : Filesystem ib-nfs_backup is occupied 90.43%
column11: Issue: ELK - NFS backup drive was running on high disk usage Impact: This will impact the backup process of ELK and can result in high disk usage on Data nodes as old indices will not be deleted Analysis: We had a request to restore an old snapshot which lead to high disk usage on backup drive. Resolution: To manage the space in NFS_drive we deleted the snapshot for the current week as indices were still alive. Archived the old snapshot backup-2018.01.22. Also, space on the backup drive is increased from 1TB to 4TB. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, problem ticket is not required as due to a request to restore old snapshot the space on Backup drive was high. This incident can be avoided?: Yes, can be avoided. Now we have allocated more space on the backup drive to avoid such issues in future.

column6: LINUX_sun - nfsla.ib : Filesystem datapro-ib_nfs_backup is occupied 90.26%.
column11: Issue: ELK - High NFS disk space. Analysis: we analyses that on the disk there were more number of snapshots that should not be there. Business impact: If there would be less space in the NFS drive then backup tool will not perform it's activities, thus there would be no snapshot creation, index deletion and archival. there could a huge impact of data mismanagement. Resolution: we removed the latest snapshot and archived the oldest snapshot so that we can have more space on NFS Disk. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as the disk space issue is not raised frequently. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as the NFS backup is includes snapshot and we don't have a fixed size of the snapshots.

Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: ####<feb 26, 2018 12:47:57 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519645677184> <BEA-310002> <50% of the total memory in the server is free> Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

column11: Issue: ELK - User was not able to see logs in Kibana Analysis: During the initial analysis of the issue, the dashboard which user was looking for in KIbana was working for us and all the nodes in ELK platform were up and running. However, later the requests to Kibana were not going through and in logs we checked that the OutOfMemoryerror were found on client nodes. Impact: Requests through Kibana were not getting responded to and hence it impacted the logs or reports users were looking at in KIbana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch on client nodes and started going through the flow. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes were overloaded which caused the outofmemory error and resolved after restarting the client nodes. HOwever, as the user base of the ELK platform is increasing and hence the load on the lcuster, we will need to increase the RAM on CLient nodes. Is this incident can be avoided: No, as the client nodes were experiencing high volume of request this incident cannot be avoided. We can increase the RAM on the client nodes as the user base of ELK platform is increasing.

column11: [SSI] Hablamos con la usuaria por télefono. Al no estar en la red de Iberia, el ordenador no ha actualizado la contraseña. Cambiamos la contraseña de Belén por teléfono y pedimos que se conecte el VPN de producción para sincronizar la nueva contraseña en el ordenador y aplicaciones (Outlook, Skype, carpetas NAS...). La usuaria no puede conectarse a VPN producción al no tener instalado el plugin F5. Comprobamos con Belén que puede conectarse al VPN que le interesa para trabajar y le proporcionamos en enlace de internet para acceder a su correo a través de OWA. De momento, al no estar en la red de Iberia, la usuaria acepta la solución proporcionada. Una vez vuelva a España, ya le hemos indicado a Belén que deberá conectar su ordenador a un cable LAN con la red de Iberia antes de encenderlo para que se sincronice la contraseña correctamente. Con su confirmación, cerramos la incidencia

column6: OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL
column11: Issue: Error encountered during execution of Partial Reversal File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution is critical to Iberia cards since it holds data of the active customers in Spain based on which business rules are created to calculate the accrued points, programs etc. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully load the partial reversal file. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

column11: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso D18OTERC Impact: Media, es un proceso diario que genera el informe de venta directa (INTERNET+SERVIBERIA+ATO'S/CTO'S). Root Cause: En el programa D18PVD1E se enfrenta un fichero que contiene los documentos con el fichero de la venta diaria. No existe uno de los documentos en el fichero de venta diaria, se trata de un documento con CPUI = SVVV , un trayecto de tipo SURFACE. Steps Taken: Eliminación del documento de tipo SURFACE del fichero ED18.ATCT004.D1802027 . Relanzar el proceso desde el paso fallado. Termina OK.
